    <item>
      <title>Don&#39;t look back</title>
      <link>https://jinnycho.github.io/blog/spirited-away/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 07 Jun 2019 00:48:01 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jinnycho.github.io/blog/spirited-away/</guid>
      <description>I often look back what I&amp;rsquo;ve done. It usually involves pretty bad regret and self-degradation. It can be about my career, relationship or my whole life. These regrets slowly change how I perceive or behave. This change can be simply forgetting my name but it can also be reshaping my whole identity to be a pig.
Re-watching an animation I watched when I was 9 was quite deeply enlightening. It was 17 years ago but I pretty clearly remember the smell of my friend&amp;rsquo;s house, smile of my friend&amp;rsquo;s mom and pure love I had to people and life.</description>
    </item>
    
